Task B — Button Press Type Detection

Author: Malaika Batool
Reg No: 23-NTU-CS-1044 Date: 26-10-2025

1. Objective

Detect short and long button presses using an ESP32:

Short press (<1.5 s): Toggle LED

Long press (>1.5 s): Activate buzzer

OLED shows press type and current state

2. Hardware Setup
Component	Pin	Function
Button	GPIO14	Input (press detection)
LED	GPIO16	Toggle on short press
Buzzer	GPIO25	Beep on long press
OLED	SDA → GPIO21, SCL → GPIO22	Display messages

All buttons use INPUT_PULLUP mode.

3. Software Overview

Uses Adafruit_SSD1306 and Adafruit_GFX for OLED.

Detects press duration using millis().

If <1500 ms: toggles LED and shows “Short Press”.

If ≥1500 ms: sounds buzzer and shows “Long Press”.

Includes debounce to prevent false readings.

4. Testing

✅ OLED shows “Ready…” at start
✅ Short press → LED toggles
✅ Long press → Buzzer sounds
✅ Messages update correctly

5. Summary

A simple project demonstrating button timing, digital I/O, buzzer control, and OLED feedback on ESP32.